comment: Professor Ames is extremely disorganized. She continuously forgets and changes the guidelines for all of her projects. It is hard to connect each of the assignments to each other and to the course which makes it difficult to follow along. Many of the assignments are easy but definitely time consuming and annoying. I would not take her again.

he's a nice professor overall, but when it comes to lectures they're super long and a lot of material is being given out. There's 2 quizzes, 2 projects, midterm, and a final. You have to take proper notes on both the lectures and the lab. He informed the class that if we did not buy cengage then he wouldn't penalize us. The class is not an easy A.

Decently fair professor. He does give you the info you need to pass, but it's not fun and it's more work than it needs to be for this course. His projects and tests are hard. His lectures are extremely boring and he is sometimes condescending. He constantly yells at my class to pay attention.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: I took Prof. Abjabbouli for python and I have to admit he really knows what he is talking about! He does go a bit fast but if you speak up and say something he will slow down and explain it again. but be ready for his tests they hard very difficult especially the midterm. make sure to listen very closely also. Good Luck and Take him!!!!

Professor Aljabbouli is such a great person. I took this class during my freshman year and even though I'm not that great with computers I still passed with a good grade. Even if you don't understand how to do certain things he's always there to help.
Amazing professor! He teaches Python through fun and engaging exercises and almost every assignment is extra credit. A fun class where you'll learn and enjoy using Python.

He's a great teacher. He talks very clearly, loud, and sometimes fast. If you ask him to slow down he will, which is great. Everything is pretty self explanatory sometimes, and sometimes its confusing. It just takes some time and some outside practice to figure out whats going on. He gives extra credits, but you just have to pay attention.

Hes a good teacher for Software I but you cannot transfer anything to Software 2 because the requirements of the project are not same. Take him to learn anything else. What he teaches in Software I will not transfer over!

I took him for Intro to Algorithms and he's not a bad guy like people seem him to be. He explains things very clearly. His test are freaking HARD! He curves though! If you want to really learn, take Al-Jabbouli!
I liked him for discrete. Took the time to show us until we understood. His exams were a bit challenging but you'll live. You don't need the textbook. He saved me 300 bucks

I took this class online and I have to say he was not that bad. He put very helpful things to help understand the material. I never got to meet him but he is a very understanding person if you email him. His exams are challenging but he gives us problems we have to face in real life. I liked him. Would recommend if you are willing to do the work.

I added him to this site so I could warn you not to take him. Way too hard for an intro class. He is there for help & you don't need the textbook but he's hard to understand and goes way too fast. Not worth it for a Gen Ed requirement. Too hard.

He is such a nice and caring professor! It is a very low-pressure class. He really wants his students to learn and do well. Imparts a lot of pratical and interesting business knowledge and advice. I HIGHLY recommend you take him!!

The sweetest person ever, honestly this professor wants you to pass his class with an A. He will even give people a second chance to re-submit an assignment just to give them a better grade. You can be absent up to 3 times and he won't count it against you.

I recommend taking Professor Freier in the summer, class goes by quick and we mostly focus on Glo-bus on our own instead of teams. Helps you with Glo-bus if you don't understand. Gives taken home quizzes. Knows a lot about what he's talking about. For sure take him. Cares a lot about his students.

Easy A. Requires textbook & attendance. Basically if you show up and do well on Glo-bus you will get an A. Quizzes are open notes. All the homework answers are in the book and if you don't do well on them he lets you redo them.

He's a sweet old man! This class was a breeze, yet I still learned a lot. Basically this class is Glo Bus, some lecture (he prints you out notes), online homework with the book and some easy open book quizzes. If you ask for help with Glo Bus he will give you tips. Our final was the week before and it was just his regular quiz! Take him!!!!!!!!!!

The sweetest and nicest professor at MSU!! the class was interesting and fun with easy assignments. I would take this professor for every class if i could. If you don't take this professor you are missing out.

The easiest class. He lets you redo writing assignments for a better grade. He offered extra credit. We never used the textbook. He lets you out of class early. He is very understanding of students busy schedules. Just show up and do the work and you will get an A.

one of the nicest and easiest professors at rutgers. easy A.  you don't actually have to read the books.  just skim them, write 1 page of b.s. and you'll get an A.   also, has some good guest speakers.

hes a very sweet man & understands students & their stress. he can be funny even though he drags on about random topics. we do simple class assignments & get out of class early, no homework, 6 writing assign, no tests, bookonline access required but barely used it. no midterm but a final. class was a breeze considering the subject. deff recommend!

I have Professor Elkins for STATS I. She is a great teacher and is very organized. She is very sweet and is one of my all time favorite professors I've ever taken !!! Professor Elkins is kind sweet and also patient which is important considering any type of math course can be confusing. If you attend every class and pay attention you'll do fine.
easy class

I had Dr. Elkins for business statistics. I learned a lot in this class. She is very corporate and has clear explanations. She explains statistics and makes it seem easy. I would definitely take her again.
Easy class. She's a business women and definitely not a teacher which makes lectures hard to sit through. Take her and you will get an A.

She's actually a really smart women, but seems new and not comfortable with engaging students yet. With that said, she's very helpful, rarely collects homework, and the quizzes are a piece of cake. She's not tricky and genuinely wants you to do well. Easy A

Although her accent is difficult to understand at first she really is an awesome professor. She will literally bring it back to the basics or start all over if the class isnt understanding something. Her style will flaw you she is so awesome. You will get frustrated with her and she will call you out but its to help YOU! I would take her again!

She is a very friendly and very helpful professor. This class was all observations so she only had class once every other week in order for us to complete our hours! Would take this professor again if she taught other classes!
Easy class but she is rude to her students
So nice

She seemed cool in the beginning but turned out to be rude and gives a lot of attitude- calls people out like they are dogs instead of students. Easy A though.. I mean, it is freshman seminar. Also don't buy the textbook!!
Great clasd
so nice ! :)

Took it cuz I liked, native American culture now I am an anthropology minor, needless to say I loved the class. You read every week, but I really just wrote in  form major parts, like an outline. If I could I would so take him over again. He really knows what he is doing and makes it interesting.

She is funny in a nerdy kind of way. Her lectures would be boring if she did not try to make a joke here and there. I wish I took her class in a lecture hall, it would of been so much more enjoyable. Her assignments were not extremely hard just watch the lectures and give in a effort.

Prof. Ambler is a really nice lady! Her class can be a little boring but there are so many chances to fix your grade. She can be a little stingy on the journal grades even though they are kind of our own opinion but it's not bad. The material was a major bore though. Google will be your best friend!!!!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: You're really missing out if you don't take her! I've never liked history, but she changed that for me. Hesitant at first, I took Dr. Ambler's online course, and I'm very happy that I did because Dr. Ambler's lectures are informative and very enjoyable to watch. Her assignments are very reasonable. Definitely wish she taught more classes!
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures--Would take again

comment: Easy A as long as you do all the work.  The written assignments are the toughest part, but even they aren't that difficult.  The lectures are a little dry, but that goes for all the online classes I've taken.

Best professor that I have ever taken! Her online classes are super easy, and books are not required, which is a plus! She has weekly lectures and every two weeks a quiz is given; it really helps out if you take notes. There are about 3 reading quizzes in which you read primary documents and it's really easy! I totally recommend her!

Easiest online class ever. the way it works is she posts powerpoints with her talking in them, and then you take a quiz every two weeks and a journal assignment thats a page long every three weeks. other than that, there is one three page paper on a movie like the gladiator. i emailed her once and responded so quickly. def take this class, easy A

Nice guy. Sometimes a little cold or short with students, but very clear, concise, and willing to help. Would take him again in a heart-beat. Exams are fair. Always willing to meet and help you. Overall, a very solid prof!

I love her!!!!! She made me love to write. Her essay topics are controversial but broad so its easy to write a paper. We also spend a lot of time working on drafts so that the final essay is good to go. Her sense style is also really nice too lol

She is, by far, one of my favorite professors that I have had so far. She's young and easy to relate to, so that makes class even more enjoyable. She is super helpful and gives you a lot of advice on how to improve your papers. I wish I could take her again for the spring semester, but her class filled up so quickly.
She was a great teacher. Her class was extremely easy and she was always so helpful! Tried to take her for 106 but her classes got full instantly! I  definitely recommend her
She gives a lot of essays but she's so nice and funny. Would definitely take her again.

wow, emily lagg is an amazing teacher. class would consist of talking about the readings that were for homework. in every class she would break everything down for you. everything was so clear. if you emailed her she would email you back right away. is considerate of your work. fair grader. i received A's in all my papers. so nice and approachable.
Very smart in most subjects, but is not very intuitive when it comes to teaching a ballet class!
Not friendly.

Took this class as an elective having never danced in my life, just liked watching dance. She expects everyone to know everything about dance as if they've been dancing forever. Very tough grader. Every assignment MUST address something in the book and even if you literally quote from the book she finds something wrong with the assignment.
Great professor, very helpful. I would take him again.  Gives multiple choice questions after each chapter, 2 Group Presentations, plus Glo-Bus game.

Solid professor and incredibly knowledgeable but my ONLY caveat here is the class, in that, as a someone who was here because they're going for Physical Education Degree and NOT athletic training I felt HEAVILY out of place here. The information presented is very heavy and this class, at least to me, felt way too advanced for what I need.
ratingTags: Respected--Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy

comment: Hes a great professor, his grading criteria is clear. He has homework but its nothing to heavy. There are two tests and are completely open ended but he sends you a study guide and as long as you study off of it you should do just fine. Hes also not a tough grader so most assignments its easy to get a good grade.
ratingTags: ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: The class itself will require you to work and read in order to pass, its physiology after all. Dr Hosick is knowledgable in his field and always willing to answer your questions. The lectures are at times dull but he does he best to keep things interesting. Highly recommend you take any course he is teaching.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: Literally the best teacher i've ever had in the history of ever

Dr. Hosick is a good professor. Lectures are long and dragged but the guy means well. I can honestly say that he is there for you when you need the help. He's willing to sit with you for 2 hours if needed if you are still not clear on a certain issue. He has a sense of humor. He is without a doubt the best option for a professor for Phys of Ex.

It was his first time teaching the class. The way the class was run was different from any other class. Be prepared to read the chapters prior to class. Class was more on discussion at first than an actual lecture. Towards the end of the semester he started using powerpoints.

Dr. Hosick is a great professorteacher. I highly recommend him for anyone who has to take physiology of exercise. He makes sure you understand the material, and is very patient. In addition he has a great sense of humor.

Dr. Dacey was really good. Our class was Thursday nights until 1045, and we rarely left early, but she made it worth while. Wasn't lecture heavy, rather all about discussions and activities, which made the class so much better. Few assignments, but they were manageable and always coincided with what we were learning. Loved the final project!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring

comment: This class was from 8:15pm-10:45pm and she rarely let us out early. You needed the text books for some assignments but not all. Participation is mandatory. She did not give any tests or finals. Just one large project at the end of the semester which ended up being really fun. She is such a kind and helpful professor!!!

Professor Dacey is a rare gem of a professor. Dacey strategically establishes her course and collaborative classroom to illustrate to pre-service teacher the best pedagogically practices for today's classrooms. She is the only teacher who has EVER ended every class with a firm hand shake to every student.

I am a continuing ed student, working on my 3rd masters degree .  Over the past 20 years i have attended multiple universities in 4 states and pursued 3 career paths.  This professor is one of the most dynamic, creative and empowering of all my professors.  Most importantly, she trusted us and established supportive community almost immediately!
Good. Knowledgeable.
Class is interesting and fun. Professor encourages students and inspires students in my different areas.

Professor Dacey was hands down the best professor I have taken in undergrad and grad school. She is such an inspiration to anyone studying to become a teacher. I loved how she happy to change up the syllabus to fit our needs. For example, after the election she helped us create lesson plans that our students would understand.  Amazing person & prof

Mrs. Dacey is one of the most well-respected professors I have ever had at Montclair State. She is approachable, and friendly - there is no disconnect between teacher & student. I would take every opportunity to have Mrs. Dacey as my professor.

Professor Dacey is kind, passionate, and sincerely cares about all of her students. She made class fun and interesting and I always looked forward to it (even though it was from 8:15-10:45pm). She is very understanding and fair. She takes the time to get to know her students on a personal level, which I really respect. Definitely recommend!
AMAZING TEACHER! Would take again and again. Very knowledgeable and is their for her students even after the semester is over.
I really enjoyed this class. If you'll willing to learn and participate in class, anyone can do well.
It was a great experience, and well worth working for it.  Charity was respectful and fair, and if she taught a class I needed, I woul definitely take it.
GOOD BALANCE BETWEEN LECTURES AND GROUP ACTIVITIES. TESTS WERE TAKEN INDIVIDUALLY AND THEN POINTS ARE ADDED IN A TEAM ROUND BUT THIS IS ONLY HELPFUL IF YOU ARE IN A GOOD GROUP WHERE PEOPLE  READ.

Charity wants all students to succeed. Being a summer course, all projects and assignments had to be condensed; there was a lot of work to be completed in a short amount of time. However, while challenging, I found the coursework interesting and relevant. I sincerely looked forward to this class. An updated text would be welcomed.
One of the best! Clear, interesting, and I learned so much about typical and atypical development in this class. Thoughtful and very engaging hands on activities. I highly recommend her!

The amount of work seems overwhelming at first, but it's really not. Pace yourself and she's very understanding with due dates. Most of our assignments were due the last day of class, which allows you to work on assignments and space them out. Very kind and easy to work with, especially with questions and last minute changes.
Was a very personable teacher who was passionate about what she was teaching. Assignments were all manageable and didn't require an exhaustive effort.
Charity was a great professor! She really helped me and guided the class though each paper. She held great discussions and I really learned a lot. Take her, you won't forget it!
There is a lot of work for a one month hybrid class but she will help you though it and I learned a great deal about assessment as a future teacher.
Expects a lot of reading but discussions are interesting.
Just bad. And confusing. Doesn't explain material in depth. Probably won't learn anything but you'll get an A.

Kalan is awesome, he uses real life experience to teach and is always engaging. Participation is a MUST!!. Class is based on Midterm and Final. He is knowledgeable, interesting, funny. He likes to share his work experiences in the corporate world. He is the most approachable and helpful teacher I ever had. Take good notes. TEST BASED ON NOTES!!
Easy going and wants to see everyone pass.

I took Kelsey during the summer and she was a great professor! She cared for her students and was always willing to help. Overall we had 3 papers, which were very easy. We had an online textbook and everything was done pretty much on a computer.
I learned more about math in six weeks with her than I did my entire four years of high school.
She's AWESOME. Explains really good without giving answer. I learned a lot from her, she's really involved. I am TERRIBLE at math and I passed my quizzes and test with 90's.

Kelsey Matkowski two words! She's awesome and extremely helpful. She is very passionate in teaching and in  providing her students the best knowledge in math. If it wasn't for this girl I don't know how I would have survived! She's a math genius and explains very very well. Must take

Overall a very good professor. He likes to tell stories during class pertaining to the material we are learning. His guest speakers were interesting. Very helpful with midterm and final exam reviews. Offers extra credit for midterm. Material is kind of boring but he makes in interesting with his stories over really good professor/class.

Prof. Azzolino is hilarious with the examples he uses during lectures. He likes telling stories about different cases that he's heard about and how it applies to class. He doesn't give too much hw and is always willing to help. There was a couple discussions, a midterm, and final. Just read the chapters and study for the tests and you'll do fine.

He is very understanding when you reach out to him, but he teaches this challenging course that will make you gasp the first few weeks if they don't come first nature to you. It gets easier a little later. There was no curve this semester, so don't expect it. You MUST watch the lectures to learn the material as the txtbook was quite a lot to read

Class started off started off as any normal stat class, challenging but manageable. We use MyStatLab but, your grade is not the same on canvas. Coronavirus hit mid semester and he did not make it any easier for us. Never answered emails, final project was so hard and irrelevant to what we had been learning, and still made the final cumulative.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Beware of pop quizzes

comment: He makes STAT so much easier to understand. U don't have to be a genius in math to get an A in his class. Part of my class was online, just watch his lectures and ask questions. There are midterm, final and a group project with short homework for each chapter. It's doable to get an A as long as you keep the effort. He is very supportive!

The professor reads many of the work straight from the powerpoint in which you really don't have to watch online unless you are learning the program. Since this is an online course, most of the work isn't graded by him but the coaches. Feedback is not that useful most of the time so improving is hard. Tough grader and group projects are required.

Montclair has given this gem of a professor, he's simply amazing. I would rate him to be the best, i wish he was the program coordinator for Business Analytics program at Montclair, he goes extra mile to help the students and really appreciate the ones who wants to learn. I would take him over and over again.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Amazing lectures

comment: This professor is easily the best INFO professor I've ever taken at MSU. He is very knowledgeable and is very easy to understand. Nothing about this class is surprising. Midterm and Final are exactly what he has reviewed in class. He is very funny and will always answer your questions either in class or by email. TAKE HIM!

Had this professor for INFO365. Professor is a lenient grader, and is generous with giving you higher marks as long as you did the work. Projects are what help your grade, didn't have any tests-- just group projects, and he takes attendance. Good professor, material is just hard. If you need a generous grader and easy assignments, take him

Hybrid class. Online portion was watching his lectures. I had to watch his lectures online to learn in his class. Midterm, Final and Group Project with homework for each chapter we discuss in class. He is a little boring but he does make stats easier.

The professor is not hard at all, but statistics in general is. He is a good professor and gives extra credit pop quizzes every once in a while. The hw can be difficult so use the "view an example" feature on pearson it will really help. There's also an easy group project as well that took me 20 mins to do. He cares for his students and it shows

PAY ATTENTION. Statistics is hard, no matter what professor you take. He is a HEAVY lecturer, however, he explains everything brilliantly and will answer any questions. There are only two exams, midterm and final. They are hard, you have to study. But if you don't miss class and pay attention to everything he says.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Dr. K is the best math teacher I've had in my academic career. The class was 7:00-9:30 but other than that he is amazing. He is very good at teaching difficult concepts and explains things until you get it. He is also funny if you listen closely. Homework is long but easy and final was take home. comment: class was 7-930pm. this prof continued teaching until class is over at 930 no exceptions. comment: Lectures regularly run close to the full 2.5 hours but they are informative. The class is stats in excel with some analytics and visualization. HW/Quizzes are online. The class is mostly instructional with some real examples. He is very helpful if you meet outside of class. If you use study plan, then you don't need a tutor. Do the HW well and you will do well in the exam.

comment: Homework can be a little hard  because he covers examples in lecture but the textbook and software is helpful. His notes were always online as well as other helpful stuff. comment: reads word for word off the slides. make sure you read the text book because that is the only way you will learn. however, he allows you to bring a sheet of paper and use your textbook during exams. the exam is similar to the homework questions so as long as you do well on the homework assignments and take good notes, it shouldn't be hard to fail

I think if I had to take statistics from anyone else I would have dropped out. He gives clear explanations but sometime it is repetitive. To make yourself known, you need to do the work, do the best, do what he states he likes to see in the class, and participate in class. Be warned tho, the class becomes more time consuming with each week. Got aA
SUPER BORING! would not take him again, taught myself everything. Homework is the only way you'll pass and understand what he is talking about. Lets you use a sheet with formulas for the two tests

He is a great professor and really teaches from his many years of experience in management. I really learned a lot when it comes to real business in this class. The game is hard, and you really have to get your team to agree with you which is more harder. taught me a lot. He is good with students and give  fair grades  and plenty of extra credit.

Professor Kollikkathara was very nice but his classes were boring. I took him for statistics and as long as you do the homework and can teach some of the information to yourself you will do well. He takes attendance once every two to three classes. He grades very leniently and you can easily get an A if you prepare a good notes sheet for the exams.

Nice professor. Helps to simplify statistics which honestly I was not a fan of in the beginning. Craks funny jokes but you to have listen to catch it. attend class and ask help for homewk and you will be fine

Homework is the biggest thing to focus on if you need to pass. The homework is basically one assignment a week, and you really need to work on the homework to pass. The homework is the biggest part of your grade. I spent 1-2 hours a week on homework, and got a B+ I would recommend this teacher if you dont get confused easily, and can teach yourself

Not one of the best professors but if you are willing to put your time and effort into the homework then you should be able to receive a decent grade. The lectures are not helpful, but if you ask for help he will help. He moves quickly with the lessons. I would recommend 3-4 hours  a week for the homework, and you basically have to teach yourself.

You can tell he is a new teacher, reads off power points. Does not clearly explain anything or interact. Does not let u make up homework and does not curve tests. Office hours are no help. Taught myself all the material. Would not take take again or recommend. Grade is basically final and midterm and he does not help prepare u for it.

He is very funny if you hear his comments. The problem is that nobody can pay attention because the lectures are so boring. He reads off the slides completely and they can be confusing to look over after. The tests are tough but I'm sure that if you pay attention you'll do fine. Overall he is an ok teacher, only because he is boring.

super cool guy but it is hard to pay attention during his lectures because he just reads off his powerpoints. less than 5 things graded for the semester but they are not hard so if you pay attention a little bit and study youll be fine.

The class can get confusing if you do not focus. Make sure to take notes and do the homework. He usually puts the slides up on canvas which can be helpful. The online homework is the most helpful in my opinion because it has examples to guide you through your work.

You can  tell that he is a new professor. uses power points from online and only reads off those every class. There is not a lot of homework at all. Expect 1 midterm and 1 final,which are similar to the homework assignments. does not explain everything clearly and is not helpful at all. ONLY A SELF LEARNING CLASS. DOES NOT TEACH. DONT BUY TEXTBOOK.

I took the summer class. Lots of people expected less work bc it was a summer class. Lots of work. Graded on class particip/assignments, 2 globus quizzes,  1 text quiz, 2 reports, and simulation performance. Optional extra cred presentation. In the end he was pretty lenient and not as bad as people made him out to be. I have way worse this semester

He is a new professor, and it shows. Seems like a nice guy at first, but is quite honestly one of the worst professors I've ever had. Simply reads off of powerpoints from the book publisher. No unique material. Gives busy work. Large group projects. Very condescending and not accommodating. DO NOT TAKE if you value your time or GPA. Terrible prof

This is an online course and it's a lot of work. Each week there are 2 discussion questions and 1 assignment. There is a super long paper that requires an extensive amount of research. 2 quizzes and a final that are really easy and multiple choice. She can be a tough grader, but just write a lot and answer all parts of the question and you're good

This is an online course and is a lot of work. Each week there are 2 discussion questions and 1 assignment. She can be a tough grader, but just write a lot and answer all parts of the question and you're good

More of a RockJazz 7-string guitarist, & also not having picked up my classical guitar in years, he inspired & worked with me to find ways to use my instrument in both ways that fulfilled instrumental criteria & also in practice. Understanding of my special needs. He's relaxed, but you WANT to play well! Very much enjoyed being his student!

for a new student seminar class, she seems like a pretty chill professor to take. as long as you show up to class, do the homework assignments, and participate, you should pass the class. she is not a tough grader AT ALL. easy A

Arguably the best professor to have for NSS! She starts every class off by going over the rubric for the semester, good for reminders. She got us a lot of guest speakers, therefore we had little work. If you need help, she checks her email once a day, but no help is ever really needed. Do her a favor and show up ON TIME for class.

He taught the lab portion of my chemistry class, and he was very clear about the criteria and always helped when students had questions. He held students to a certain standard so doing quality work on time is important. Very nice and knowledgable.

"Waitt Craig!"   He's an ok teacher but a great person.  Responds back to emails in a reasonable time. We made silly putty. He is always available when you need him as well as open to tutoring outside of class time. If you know nothing about science then the exams are hard. Therefore you should study.  Fashion majors beware; you're in for a scare!

He was fantastic. He was helpful, patient and kind to each of his students. Even though my lecture class was behind in the labs, he took the time to teach us what our lecture professor hadn't. He has a great personality and is always willing to help, but also encourages you to think for yourself. He made the lab class a great experience.

This was my lab professor and he was AMAZING! He is always willing to help you and he won't give up until you understand it. The labs are pretty easy, just do the prelab and read the lab and you're fine. He was always nice and funny and his labs were enjoyable. If you don't understand something in lecture he is willing to help you out!

He was my lab professor and he's amazing and a wonderful funny personality. Always happy whenever you have him for lab . He's always willing to help whenever you need it he even offers to tutor you. The labs are quite interesting and always quite easy. Best lab professor that you can have hands down
Super easy class, just do the work. Interesting subject and hes literally so funny and one of my fav professors Ive ever had
She is great but she needs to stop doing group work every class. She is always willing to help your grade

Gives a lot of homework and online assignment but it only helps with ur grade if u do poor on one exams. Plus theres extra credit. The amount of homework and assignments can be annoying but it was a fun experience.

Prof Lacey is great and really cares about her students and wants to see them do well. There are a bunch of homework due every week and some misc assignments and group work every now and then but not too hard if you're good at Spanish. Lectures are very group heavy so make sure you make friends quick because you'll be working with them all semester

Tough but not too bad. I was afraid I would struggle but I have an A in the class and it is November. She does a lot of group work and makes us sit in assigned groups. There is a lot of homework and quizzes, a midterm and final and myspanishlab. Study and participate a lot. You are graded on how much you speak spanish. She will help you !

She cares about her students and wants them to do well. Myspanishlab homework after every class. Online textbook is mandatory. Class is basically group work from the textbook, which is made difficult since she doesn't teach much. Mostly self-teaching from the textbook. Not that hard of a class but make sure to participate or you get called on.
Shes a great professor! make sure to ask questions if you need help! She genuinely cares and hates to see students fail. I recommend this class.
There is a lot of myspanishlab homework.  She also posts lectures ahead of time and grades your at home notes in the beginning of class.  She is sweet and cares about everyone.

Prof. Lacey is awesome.  Her class is so easy if you just pay attention and ask for help if you need it.  She loves her job and makes a clear connection with each student.  She drops the lowest quiz grade, but if you study what she tells you that won't matter anyway.  TAKE HER! Class is not boring and she's super cute and asks for help in english.
She is one of those people that actually like her job! She will always help those who struggle and is so understanding. She plays games, gives you many chances to pass and is just amazing.
Professor Gifis is so sweet and such a nice person! Her class was really easy and I enjoyed coming to class every week. I would definitely take her again! She's awesome!

I took this class on accident and I'm so happy I did! Prof Gifis is awesome! She is young and is very understanding. You do write a lot of papers in the class, but no tests, except for a final exam that was super straight forward. Learned a lot! Turned out to be my favorite class of the semester.

Professor Giffs's is awesome! She communicates through email, which she responds to very quickly. She does not make the readings mandatory, but they are necessary for in class discussions. If you do not participate, she will assign quizzes! Cancels class at times due to her kids. No midterm, 1 final, 1 big group project, and a few easy assignments.

first semester teaching. so she had to figure stuff out but clearly passionate about her subject. happy to speak to students outside of class. speaks fast. and her tests are not easy, but don't think any art history tests are easy. i hear they all make you memorize, it sucks. but thats what you have to do apparently.
These were her exact words: "I understand that English is not everyone's first language, but at Montclair it is" So basically too bad.

If you have no other choice then go for it. Her class was very long. you even get a quiz a week before the final. The museum paper is due a week before the final. which the whole class thought should be marked as the final since it was so long. this is one of the hardest classes I have taken. She is very sassy

Most students in the class seem afraid to answer the questions she ask because ,she tells you that you're wrong in a negative way. If she smiled, and allowed students to express how they feel about an art painting or sculpture then more students would participate in class discussions. Another thing is her tests are very hard and not precise at all.
She isn't very clear with the lessons. All we talk about are pieces of art off of a power point which makes the class pretty boring. Alot of artists and art pieces to memorize.

I took his online class and it was less than pleasant. Nice guy but doesn't seem to translate well online - its not helpful when all he does is upload a bunch of readings and expects you to understand it. Midterm review was useless - just a bunch of broad topics with little guidance. In person he may be better, but beware if online!
AMAZING!! He's the reason why I decided to get my masters in Social Work. Everything I know was from him.  Wish he taught more CHAD classes.

Professor Freid is a amazing professor! As long as you read, take notes, and study you will get an A. He keeps class very interesting. He works as a prosecutor in the special victims unit so he tells you real child abuse stories which really helps you learn the material. I learned so much from him. I would definitely take this class again!!

This was one of the best classes I have ever taken. Professor Fried is very helpful and will always answer any questions you have. There is two quizzes, a midterm and a final. As long as you read, go to class, take good notes, and study then there is no reason to not get an A. If you really want to learn about children justice then take this class!

AMAZING PROFESSOR!!! He knows he's stuff!!!! Keeps it very interesting... Tells you exactly what he expects which is reasonable considering that you are a college student.. I learned so much... RECOMMEND HIM...I would DEFF take him again.

Can be harsh, for example tells you "that's wrong'" if he feels that you are not giving him the answer that he wants. Gives exams!!! Too many chapters to study for exams. Does not promote class discussion.

Took him for Psych 101. His class was my favorite to go to. His lectures included not only the material from the book but in feild as well. After an exam he would hold a break day for a movie psychology related.  Awesome professor his grading scale is easy to understand, expect a quiz every week, and the only downside was his long exams.

His online course was by the far the worst one I have ever taken. 200 question midterms? it was way too much work for an online class. I would never take this class again or let anyone I know and love take it either.

Professor Lee is super sweet and cutesy, but beware! Her tests are extremely hard and she teaches material way beyond the scope of the class-which makes the final that much easier. If you can pass her class, you might just be set for life. Aural skills was a lot better, though.
For aural skills, you're going to have to practice. But you do a lot of work in class. She expects quite a bit from you, but is very supportive and is a very fair grader.
Professor Lee is a great Theory teacher. She knows what she is talking about!

Easy A! He is very boring and talks a lot. The speech topics are very easy. Makes you do unnecessary things that are pointless. Just show up. Only 4 speeches and a couple papers which are easy. No group project which other speech teachers give. Take him if you want an easy a for a gen ed.

No help at all. He has no idea what he is talking about half of the time and just about every class he will do random exercises making everybody speak in front of the class about random things. Do not take his class.

He often is so confused and losses track of his thoughts. At least the first 10 minutes of class are spent on breathing exercises and he often talks about how much anxiety he has. Almost every class you have to get up and speak for at least a minute about random topics. Other than being so confused he also is monotone and could put you to sleep.
He has a hard time forming his thoughts. He is old and forgetful. He is always so disoriented and unaware of what is going on. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS/
He gives monotonous lectures and is not very clear with his points.

Do NOT take this professor. I absolutely love music and he made my FAVORITE subject so boring. He is also rude and all he does is talk and play clips the entire hour. One time reached over and nearly snatched a student's phone out of her hand because he got fed up that so many people were on their phone. He's also very unclear on what he wants.

This guy made music class, which I was most excited about going into he year, by far my least favorite class.  He is very condescending and rude- and be prepared to have to listen to him annoyingly sing every. single. class.  I would STRONGLY advise not having this guy be your music professor, he's really just terrible.
first year teaching  and didnt know how to work the technology at all. Needs to give students a better way to take notes because he doesnt have a powerpoint. Gets off track and goes extremely fast.

Although I got an A in this class, this professor isn't easy. The test are nothing like the homework and I studied very hard for this class. You have to know excel to pass this class. He curves a lot. He looks like Santa Claus and speaks in a monotone voice that will easily put you to sleep. Overall study hard and do the work and make friends.

It's a Statistics class. You're not likely going to find a professor who can make this topic exciting. That being said, he reads off slides and doesn't sound excited to be there. BUT, he knows what he's saying, the slides he reads off of help when it comes to homework and studying for exams which we can use. Great guy, not a great a professor.

Dan is a very nice guy, but I don't recommend taking his statistics class. The lectures are beyond boring, and most of the material has to be self taught. He does not properly explain how to use excel and other programs to do assignments and work, so I would recommend making friends. The homework is not easy. Wouldn't take again.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: His classes are really boring, you'll fall asleep immediately He talks about concepts but doesn't even explain how to put it in practice when he gives excel homework, if it wasn't because I know how to use excel very well I will be failing.

By far the worst professor in the Feliciano School of Business. A terrible teacher with a terrible attitude outside of class. Montclair needs to fire him because he is too old to be a professor and he barely teaches.
He looks like santa claus but he is anything but jolly. I have fallen asleep multiple times.

Professor Ericson is a nice guy and semi-decent professor but the classes are very boring lectures that go over the slides. All of the homework is online on Pearson, and is not covered in class. Buy PHStat because it will help you a lot with the homework. Tests are pretty hard, but if you do a lot of practice you should be good.
He doesn't teach anything he only goes over slides with vocabulary but doesn't teach the math equations that going to be on the test.

Do not take this professor. I am a straight A student, who does their homework & shows up to class & I am struggling. All he does is stand & read powerpoints of the vocab in the book. He does not explain how to do the math calculations. I have to teach myself how to do the homework. He is very boring & speaks so slow. He shouldn't be a teacher.

He is a really nice guy. Lectures are long and boring but then again its a statistics class.  The tests are hard if you do not study but he allows you to use a cheat sheet.  The project is very difficult but if you go to the tutoring center they will help you.

Lectures are extremly long. The project given will be a long term project that goes throughout the whole class. Very confusing. You will need mystatlab. Never opened the text book and phstat was a WASTE OF MONEY! This class is so expensive. Powerpoints are posted online. You take 3 exams. Only benefit is he drops lowest exam grade. Do hw and study!

One of the nicest professors I have had. Lectures are long but easy environment. Make sure to do his homework or you will not pass. Always gives big curve on test to bring up class average. Could be very boring at times but I would recommend taking his class. Easy grade if you do the work.
Decent professor, you don't need to buy PHStat. Microsoft excel can do all the functions PHStat does. He speaks very slowly which can be annoying but he's a nice guy.

He did not do many problems on the board just explained what the outcomes could be if the number was a negative, 0 or positive.  He talks from the powerpoint, very boring   I had to go back to my old school to get extra help and basically taught the class on my own.   There were lots of extra fees to the class- $100 mystatlab, $10 phstats & book.

Prof. Ericson  was a new prof during fall semester 2015. He dropped the lowest test grade and all hw assignments were on MyStatLab. They were pretty easy with the help of the examples provided. There was also one project on a "bad" graph.  He also allows one sheet with any info for tests. If you study, then youll do well.

Very nice professor, there are 9 easy but long homework assignments on Mystatlab and one presentation. Only 3 exams and he drops the lowest one, you are allowed to bring a cheat sheet. He's also willing to help you if you have any questions. He posts all the lectures on Canvas. Overall good professor and easy A, I highly recommend.

She is extremely educated and helpful in opening the minds of students. I enjoy every minute of her class and find the content to be really interesting and informative. Honestly she should be teaching a higher level course.
This was a pottery I took for my general requirement art category class. She is very nice, really funny, and really helps students understand the basics of ceramics and pottery.

Professor Ossandon is a really cute and quirky lady. She is really helpful, but at the same time she always lets you do your own thing, even if it might not be the way that she would do it. I really appreciate that she isn't so intense about doing things the right way rather she wants you to do them your way. I would highly recommend her!

I took Prof. Mejil's online child abuse class and could tell she is very kind. Unfortunately, she is very hard to contact because she rarely answers emails in a timely manner and even suggested texting her which was weird. This class was A LOT of work. I would suggest not taking if it's not a requirement. Her grading does not make much sense.

I took Professor Levin as my first online class and was very satisfied with this class. He is the nicest Professor out there and is very organized with his modules. He states exactly what he expects from his students in the assignments and they really are not all that bad. Just put in effort and manage your time with the class and you'll do great!

He's a great Professor! I took his online Historical Foundations of American Education and it was a super easy A. Every week we have a discussion/work and lot of readings, so definitely time management is important! He's an easy grader so as long as you do what your suppose to do, you'll definitely pass! I would want to take him again!
ratingTags: Respected--Get ready to read--Clear grading criteria

comment: His work was difficult and time consuming. Its a lot of reading & writing. If you miss a discussion, you will be graded in the negatives. Do your work & you will pass. He is beyond nice & will help if you ask for it. He gives great feedback & really loves to teach. His class was hard but I learned a lot. Try, its not impossible.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Gives good feedback--Get ready to read

comment: This professor harassed me ALL TIMES OF THE NIGHT over his work. I missed one discussion and did not reply to his submission comments (which I would not get notifications for) so he dropped all my previous grades to a 50%. He eventually emailed me and told me I would never pass and that I should drop the course. DO NOT TAKE. YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED.

comment: Professor Levin is great. There is a lot of work in this class that mostly requires reading and responding to articles. Highly recommend!

take his online educational foundations if you can!!! easiest A i've ever had. he's very inspirational with his teaching methods. deff get the books because it was all reading and discussion posts from the book. it looks like a lot of work at first but the due dates make it completely manageable. such a sweet man who loves his students lol
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Inspirational--Clear grading criteria

comment: Absolutely loved Professor Levin. He is a sweet man who is so interested in hearing what his students find interesting. I took his history course and I learned a lot! ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: I learned a lot from Professor Levin's class. Some weeks he gives a lot of homework, and it involves a lot of reading but its manageable and its an easy A as long as you put a little effort in and manage your time well. Most assignments he lets you do again or fix if he wasn't fully satisfied the first time.  He's a really nice guy.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: I really don't understand  why he has such bad reviews on here. Yes,there is homework but it is a reasonable amount. He also allows you to correct and revise your work for full credit if he feels like something is missing. If you have any questions, you can email him and he'll get right back to you. I would take him again in a heartbeat.

Professor Levin is getting a bad rep. here. I LOVE he class, and would take him again. The is college people, you're going to get reading and work--this is probably the same amount of work as my major classes. He's a really great guy and give extra credit if he feels you did really well on something. There is also no midterm/final, which is nice.

I actually really enjoyed professor Levin's class. He answers emails right away and really cares about all his students. I will have to admit, that it once took me 10 hours to read for just one week of homework.  5-10 hours of reading of week with guarded homework but as long as you do the reading & homework, it basically a guaranteed A

His classes are lectures for every single lesson. He will talk the entire time and gives tons of homework. He will assign homework days after the class has met and gives you 2 days to do it (on the weekend!). The homework assignments take 4-5 hours every single time because there is so much reading and writing. Do not take!

This guy SUCKS he gives the most amount of homework i have ever received in my life, he is a very hard grader and its his way or the highway. readings are 3-4 hours every week and I'm not being dramatic. DO NOT TAKE this guy you will regret it every day of the semester.

This class was taken because it's a required course in order to apply to the teaching program. This was the absolute worst professor. He gives tons of reading assignments and the way he structures his assignments is super confusing. Tons of homework and quizzes and discussion post. DONT TAKE HIM. LEAVE. BEWARE.

Prof. Garcia is one of the worst professors I have ever had. As an online professor, she did not make it clear what assignments were due and never gave feedback. Also, her sign language was virtually unrecognizable where tutors couldn't even understand it. The final and midterm were worth 70% of our grade and were the only things she graded hard.

This class was really great. I was worried about it being an online ASL 1 class but Prof. Garcia made it so easy. There is a lot of homework and assignments, but it's needed. If you don't put in the work to practice and learn the material, you won't pass. Definitely would take her again if I could.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Lots of homework--Participation matters

comment: DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS ONLINE!!. YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN. Teacher does not respond to emails right away and no clear explanations given for assignments. The class structure is terrible and unless you're a fluent ASL student or understand you will FAIL. For a beginner taking this class it should not be given online. IF YOU WANT TO PASS AVOID THIS CLASS

This was an awful online class. She doesn't respond to emails, she creates several assignments per week & most are unclear & she takes forever to grade so there's very little feedback. Modules don't get posted on time & certain assignments aren't unlocked until right before they're due. Lots of partner work, which didn't work out in an online class

Dont take her online. I have a history of ASL so the class was easy for me, but if i didnt know the material Id be lost. A lot is self taught & she doesnt use her voice in videos. She assigns 5-6 assignments per week & its hard to keep track of it all. She made us do partner assignments for an ONLINE class. Upside: shes a VERY easy grader.

She teaches the class entirely in sign language, which takes some getting used to. I was getting an A the entire semester, and a week before class was over, it dropped down to a D. She did not allow me to do anything to make my grade go up. I wouldnt take her again. Much rather just go take someone who at least will speak to me in English
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Great Professor. Always do your homework and the exams are very important.
Love her so much im taking her again. Teaches mute and truly cares that students learn the language. dont get the book. attend class because she signs vocab words/sentenes

Outstanding Professor. If you truly want to learn sign language then YOU MUST take her class. Super understanding and cares about her students learning the language. Very hilarious. Teaches mute therefore you learn best!

She's an awesome teacher and will go out of her way to help you understand. She's full of energy. Be prepared to be confused the first class or two, but if you pay attention, it will begin to make sense.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious

comment: Love love love her! She teaches completely mute and even though you sometimes don't know what she is signing, you get the idea. She is very animated and hilarious! Its really important that you attend class because then you won't learn the signs that she does each week. The book isn't necessary but it helps! Definitely take her!!
LOVE HER!! great prof, really loves to sign and puts a lot of emotion behind her signs and meaning. take her, won't regret it. taking her again for AMSL 102 (mandatory)

Love her. She teaches as a mute, so you will never hear her talk. She is so sweet. Teaches at a fast pace, but she is so nice, if you need her to slow down she will. Never really gives test. No textbook. Take her for you language requirement.

Professor Prezant is such a kind lady, always willing to help you succeed. Classes were a bit boring since she just read off PowerPoints but other than that she is a wonderful woman. She gives a study guide for both tests, material on them is related to the topics on the guide. Neither tests nor paper were too bad. Midterm, final, and a paper.

I enjoyed Professor Prezan'ts class--she supplemented her powerpoints with videos and interactive websites; these helped in understanding phonetics. She did not provide a study guide for the 3 exams but did let us know what to focus on. The book was helpful--the exercises helped prepare us for the exams/homework assignments.
Professor P is very knowledgeable on the topics covered. There are several long power points but she also uses videos as a reference and examples. Fairly easy grader as well
ratingTags: GRADED BY FEW THINGS--Caring--Would take again

comment: I would definitely take Professor Prezant again! I enjoyed her lectures and how she used supplementing videos. You should definitely read the text for the tests, not just study the powerpoint slides. I found the cd to be helpful, especially in preparation for the tests.

Your grade is based off of exams and one poster project. I'm a good student and I struggled in this class. She would give us a study guide, which didn't help. I personally thought her exams were difficult. She just reads off of powerpoint slides
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Passionate about speech and language but lacks enthusiasm with lectures. Get ready to watch her read off of power points. Buy the book not the antasse cd thing. It was a waste of money

Such a sweet-heart, so helpful and clearly explains the material. She knows what she is teaching and is well organized. She lets you out early sometimes but she makes the material so interesting form watching videos and going so in depth that the class goes by quickly! Definitely take her.

Not a lot of room to mess up and take the hw seriously. Shes super nice and helpful. She gives you a study sheet for the midterm/final. Power points really help but still buy/rent the text. Test are EXACTLY whats on the review, Those who didn't get an A are those who procrastinated. Hw due once a week. She grades hw based  on quality not quantity.

Grade is based off of the midterm, final, and hw assignments (which are easy). She doesn't take attendance and puts up all the PPs on Canvas but if you miss the lectures, it'll be harder for you to learn. MUST study for the 2 exams because majority of your grade is based off of them. I'm an SLP minor and the remaining classes are in Bloomfield
We only had a few assignments. Do you best because it's not much room to mess up. She's very supportive, approachable, easy to talk to and understanding.

So-so as a professor. Very unorganized when it comes to explaining the writing assignment or reading. loves detailed writing and mushrooms! Office hours are eh - come with a lot of questions and go to the writing center as much as you can! Sometimes he is helpful other times he is not! Got a B- at the end of the semester !
Confusing grader
He is nice, and will help with your writing a lot. You have to participate a lot, if you don't, then he will call on you.

If you have to take this class as a psych major then for the love of God take it with someone else. I can honestly say that this is by far the worst college class I have ever taken to this day. She's smart and clearly has an understanding of the subject - but she cannot teach at all. If you plan on taking her, for whatever reason, good luck to you.

The class is given mainly in Spanish. There are two essays ( around 3 pages each) you have to complete, one presentation, and will participate in some class discussion; also, participation is really appreciated. In addition, he is very inspirational and funny, very understandable and caring with the students. One of the best teachers at MSU!

One of the best professors there is at MSU. Definitely should take him if you have the chance. He is the best. He cares alot about his students and is always available whenever he is needed. I would 100% take his class if you can!
Amazing! Great professor very caring and is very knowledgeable. Knows a lot about business and Spanish. Would definitely take again

Best Professor I have ever had . Amazing !! I recommend you to take him!!! He is funny, smart, respectful? And a fun and interesting person to talk to !!! Everyone in my class agrees !!!! You will have a great experience having him as a professor !!!
Hes a very caring and kind professor. He cares about students opinions. Knows your name by the first day. Gives you the PowerPoints used in class. 100% recommend
Professor McGuinness truly cares about all of his students. He will know your name by the second class and will make you laugh in every class thereafter. Great professor! Definitely take his class :)
Great class! One of very few adjuncts at that school, that's actually teaches
He's great! He really cares about the students.

This class is the hardest class, I have taken. She is a new professor so she has something to prove. When she grades papers, her feedback are not helpful but rather very sarcastic. If one is trying to pass their first level of writing class, I'd advise not to take this class.

This class is the hardest class I have ever taken in my life. There is so much work. Lugo isn't a very good professor either. She rarely gives feedback on our essay drafts. She has a bit of an attitude too. Her teaching style is over the top. She curses all the time. She's not the worst professor I ever had, but if you can avoid her do it

I personally enjoyed class discussions but I did not enjoy her teaching techniques. She does not grade papers and hands them to you late giving you no time to actually write the next draft. Tried hard to fix my writing to her expectations but I continued getting low grades.

Prof. Bachmann knows his stuff, I learned a lot from him. There's weekly reads and he will pick on people so participation is a MUST. Lectures are heavy with a lot information and would lecture through the whole class with no breaks. I feel like he can come off a little rude but thats just because he's preparing his students for the real world.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: So if you want an easy A, def not the professor for you. Gives you no breaks, a lot of reading for participation the next class and participation is a must so if you dont like speaking dont take. Oh and group projects. Ive had better professors. Wont take again.
ratingTags: Participation matters--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: He's ok. If you take him at night you will be there every second of 2hrs & 30min with no break. It's brutal and makes you not want to even learn the material. He is nice and his grading is fair but he really drags class on and on. I wouldn't take him again, but he isn't a bad professor. Lots of group work, some assignments, and then the tests.

This professor is the worse. He makes you stay in class until the exact minute you are supposed to leave. If youre in for 2 hours and 30 minutes hes generous enough to give you a 3 minute break. His lectures are never ended, constantly talking, and doesnt allows students to talk. Stay away from this professor find someone else.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: The biggest issue is that when learning a new language for class credit, you shouldn't be expected to study and put more time into learning for a mandatory language class than your own major. The problem with this professor is that if you have a spelling mistake in your entire sentence but the meaning is still obvious, your ENTIRE answer is wrong.

Fair teacher though a bit difficult at times. She is there for you if you need help and does her best to help you but won't baby you. She relies heavily on the text book and two online sites for classwork and homework. Quizzes and tests are fairly easy if you study for them. Not an awful teacher by any means but not one of the better ones.

DO NOT TAKE. Professor Cirilo was a terrible professor, especially for those who are just taking the class for the requirement and not into poetry. Why even make a syllabus when when he doesn't follow it is beyond me. And then once an assignment comes up he posts it on canvas very close to when its due. Avoid him

He's a really nice guy but his grading doesn't resemble his personality. Don't expect to get an A in this class because you have a better chance to get struck by lightning. He gave 4 essay and the average class grade was like a C... So good luck

Doesn' t seem to care about attendance, although it is hard to get more than a B, and most likely you'll get mostly C's. Willing to read drafts, and writes ample notes so you get an explanation of your grade. Has specific expectations so you have to learn and write with his criteria in mind

He is a really really nice guy, definitely cares about his students. However, he is n extremely tough grader, and it's hard to get higher than a C in his class. Some prompts were confusing, and it sucks because the second you're finished with an essay, another gets assigned.

Professor Brown is my absolute favorite professor! She is hilarious and she makes the class want to learn. I was never good at trying to learn spanish but she is very helpful. I definitely recommend her for a spanish course.

Professor Brown is such a sweetheart. She really cares about her students and wants them to do well. There is a lot of homework but it's not hard. There are 2 tests, a midterm, and a final. Participation is important, it can really make or break your grade. She's very helpful and you're guaranteed a laugh every time you step foot in her class.

Honestly my favorite professor thus far. She's so reasonable and gets you to actually understand the language. She also really cares and gets to know you as a student and is aware of your comfort zone as well as your strengths and struggles. As long as you do the work and go to class, you'll pass. Highly recommend!

Was kinda winging it on taking her since she wasn't on her but glad I did. Professor Brown is a sweetheart and absolutely hilarious. She makes me want to come to class and makes learning spanish, FUN! There is quite a bit of hw but it's mostly online and really easy. She's very helpful and clear when teaching. She's an understanding teacher.

Really great professor! Very passionate and extremely knowledgeable about the subject he teaches. A ton of reading, very important to come to class prepared & ready to participate. Participation is a huge % of grade. Great guy though, thought provoking lectures
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--Amazing lectures

comment: A great professor who I recommend to anyone taking a General Humanities or Myth course.  His lectures are funny and entertaining and he makes class not seem so boring as most professors do.  He is also a good grader and as long as you show up to class, do your work, and participate, you should have an A or B.

I had Professor Rice for the Freshman Seminar. He's a good guy. But in all truth, he's the academic advisor that doesn't advise. comment: He is one of the best professors for FINC. Although his tests are hard, he lets u use open note during the exam and always willing to help u outside of the class. Professor Izzi is a great guy. He is very helpful when you don't understand the material and always willing to help. His sense of humor makes the class a lot more bearable than it could be otherwise. Some of the material is tough, and Professor Izzi's real world experience in finance helps a ton

Exams are open book, open notes and you can use a laptop. In spite of this, the class is still challenging. hes very nice, funny, sarcastic. he treats this course as an advanced finc course & pretends like we know everything already when that is far from reality. he teaches very fast& thinks we understand everything. when u ask a question sometimes u feel like its stupid bc it comes so easy to him. he curves ALOT. open notes and book tests. sweet man.

Amazing professor! Really cares about you, your education and success. Great person, super nice! It really doesn't get better than a professor like him. He's awesome. If you just really put in effort and try your hardest you should do well.

The funniest and by far my favorite professor. He is a pretty hard grader, but makes class fun which is awesome. Definitely recommend him to anyone and everyone. If I was able to take another class with him I 100% would.

He has a thick accent, but it can eventually be understood.

There should be no reason to fail if you read and look over his handouts. He has an accent, but he is understandable. He is there for you if you need help with your papers. Took her courses at Tulane, not Montclair. Palmer is the best! Clear grader and gives good feedback, really nice, informative lectures. Laptops are allowed, which made it easier to take notes. She goes through slides and info really quickly, but posts them on Canvas. Very few tests and papers were assigned, and were extremely easy. Just do the study guides. Attendance counts! She seems a bit jittery and nervous but is very knowledgable.

Palmer is really nice. She's super laid back, although she comes off as a very nervous person. Very lax about laptops and phones, which is both good and bad because people do take advantage. She ALWAYS makes herself Available to students if they need her. Tests aren't bad. She does fly through 50 slides per lecture, and feeds you information.

she is a very nice professor and is very helpful when you call her and talk to her. however, the amount of papers she expects you to write is absolutely ridiculous. i don't think in all of my career of college i have written as many papers in total as i've had to in this one class.
